# Common Authentication Attacks

---

## Brute Force Attack

Trying many passwords against one account.

Example:

```text
admin

↓

123456

↓

password

↓

admin123

↓

qwerty
```

---

## Credential Stuffing

Using leaked usernames and passwords from previous data breaches.

Attackers assume users reuse passwords.

---

## Password Spraying

Trying one common password against many users.

Example:

```text
Password123

↓

Alice

Bob

Charlie

David
```

---

## Session Hijacking

Stealing a valid session cookie to impersonate a logged-in user.

---

## Token Theft

Stealing JWTs or API Tokens.

---

## Weak Password Policy

Examples:

```text
123456

password

qwerty

admin
```

Weak passwords are easy to guess.

